# Rule Type: Always


## Code Style & Quality
- Follow **PEP 8** style (max line length 88)
- Use **Google style docstrings** for all functions
- Include **type hints** for function signatures
- Avoid hardcoded values; use constants or configuration

## Testing
- Write **unit tests** for all new calculation or logic code
- Add **integration tests** for any new Streamlit components
- Cover edge cases and validate expected behavior thoroughly

## Error Handling
- Validate all user inputs with clear error messages in the UI
- Handle exceptions gracefully and log unexpected errors for debugging

## UI & Accessibility
- Maintain consistent dark theme and responsive layout
- Use clear labels, placeholders, and tooltips on inputs/buttons
- Ensure keyboard navigation and high-contrast colors for accessibility

## Documentation
- Update or add documentation for new features or major changes
- Include setup instructions and usage examples where relevant

## Security & Performance
- Do not embed sensitive data or API keys in the code
- Optimize performance by caching expensive calculations
- Minimize unnecessary Streamlit reruns for smooth UX